# Node.js File System

The `fs` module is the foundation of all file I/O in Node.js. Always prefer `node:fs/promises` for new code and reserve sync methods for CLI startup paths.

## Reading Files

```javascript
import { readFile } from 'node:fs/promises';
import { createReadStream } from 'node:fs';

// Read entire file as string
const content = await readFile('config.json', 'utf-8');
const data = JSON.parse(content);

// Read as Buffer (binary, no encoding argument)
const buffer = await readFile('image.png');

// readFileSync — only at startup or in CLI scripts
import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';
const pkg = JSON.parse(readFileSync('package.json', 'utf-8'));

// Stream large files (>100MB) with backpressure
const stream = createReadStream('huge-log.txt', { encoding: 'utf-8' });
for await (const chunk of stream) {
  process.stdout.write(chunk);
}
```

## Writing Files

```javascript
import { writeFile, appendFile, mkdir, rename } from 'node:fs/promises';
import { createWriteStream } from 'node:fs';
import { dirname } from 'node:path';
import { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';

// Always create parent directories first
await mkdir(dirname('output/data/result.json'), { recursive: true });
await writeFile('output/data/result.json', JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));

// Append to a log file
await appendFile('app.log', `${new Date().toISOString()} Started\n`);

// Exclusive write — fail if file already exists
await writeFile('lock.pid', String(process.pid), { flag: 'wx' });

// Atomic write: write to temp file then rename (rename is atomic on same fs)
const tmp = `config.json.${randomUUID()}.tmp`;
await writeFile(tmp, JSON.stringify(config, null, 2));
await rename(tmp, 'config.json');

// Stream writes for large output
const ws = createWriteStream('large-output.csv');
for (const row of rows) {
  if (!ws.write(row.join(',') + '\n')) {
    await new Promise((resolve) => ws.once('drain', resolve));
  }
}
ws.end();
await new Promise((resolve) => ws.on('finish', resolve));
```

## Directory Operations

```javascript
import { mkdir, readdir, rm, cp, rename } from 'node:fs/promises';

// Create nested directories in one call
await mkdir('src/components/ui/buttons', { recursive: true });

// List directory contents with type info
const entries = await readdir('src', { withFileTypes: true });
const dirs = entries.filter(e => e.isDirectory()).map(e => e.name);
const files = entries.filter(e => e.isFile()).map(e => e.name);

// Recursive listing (Node 20+)
const allEntries = await readdir('src', { withFileTypes: true, recursive: true });

// Copy an entire directory tree
await cp('src', 'backup/src', { recursive: true });

// Remove directory and all contents
await rm('dist', { recursive: true, force: true });

// Rename / move a file (same filesystem only)
await rename('old.js', 'new.js');
```

## File Stats and Existence Checks

```javascript
import { stat, lstat, access, constants } from 'node:fs/promises';

// Get file metadata
const info = await stat('package.json');
console.log(info.size, info.mtime, info.isFile(), info.isDirectory());

// Idiomatic existence check (fs.exists is deprecated)
try {
  await access('config.json');
  // file exists
} catch {
  // file does not exist
}

// Check specific permissions
await access('data.json', constants.R_OK | constants.W_OK);

// Inspect symlink itself (stat follows symlinks, lstat does not)
const linkInfo = await lstat('symlink.js');
console.log(linkInfo.isSymbolicLink());
```

## Watching Files

```javascript
import { watch } from 'node:fs/promises';

// Async iterator watch (Node 19+)
const watcher = watch('src', { recursive: true });
for await (const event of watcher) {
  console.log(event.eventType, event.filename);
}

// fs.watch (callback style)
import { watch as watchCb } from 'node:fs';
const w = watchCb('config.json', (eventType, filename) => {
  console.log(`${eventType}: ${filename}`);
});
process.on('SIGINT', () => w.close());

// For production, prefer chokidar for cross-platform consistency:
// import chokidar from 'chokidar';
// chokidar.watch('src', { ignoreInitial: true })
//   .on('change', (path) => console.log('changed:', path));
```

## Path Module Integration

```javascript
import { join, resolve, dirname, basename, extname, parse, relative } from 'node:path';
import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';

// ESM equivalent of __dirname and __filename
const __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);
const __dirname = dirname(__filename);

// Always use join — never concatenate with '/'
const configPath = join(__dirname, '..', 'config', 'app.json');

// Resolve to absolute path
const abs = resolve('relative/path/file.txt');

// Extract path components
basename('src/index.ts');        // 'index.ts'
basename('src/index.ts', '.ts'); // 'index'
extname('file.tar.gz');          // '.gz'
dirname('/usr/local/bin/node');   // '/usr/local/bin'

// Relative path between two locations
relative('/data/orandea/test/aaa', '/data/orandea/impl/bbb'); // '../../impl/bbb'

// Parse into components
const parts = parse('/home/user/file.txt');
// { root: '/', dir: '/home/user', base: 'file.txt', ext: '.txt', name: 'file' }
```

## Temporary Files and Directories

```javascript
import { mkdtemp, writeFile, rm } from 'node:fs/promises';
import { tmpdir } from 'node:os';
import { join } from 'node:path';

// Create a unique temporary directory
const tmpDir = await mkdtemp(join(tmpdir(), 'myapp-'));
// e.g. '/tmp/myapp-A1B2C3'

try {
  await writeFile(join(tmpDir, 'data.json'), JSON.stringify(data));
  // ... do work with temp files ...
} finally {
  // Clean up temp directory
  await rm(tmpDir, { recursive: true, force: true });
}
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `NODE_PATH` | Additional directories to search when resolving modules with require/import |
| `TMPDIR` / `TMP` / `TEMP` | Override default temporary directory (used by `os.tmpdir()`) |
| `HOME` / `USERPROFILE` | User home directory, used by `os.homedir()` |
| `UV_THREADPOOL_SIZE` | Controls libuv thread pool size for async fs operations (default 4, max 1024) |
